item.description:
Suppose you have two classes: 
public class Foo {
private String[] array = (String[]) new Object[];
public static void main() {
Foo f = new Foo();
}
}
public class Bar&lt;T&gt; {
private T[] array = (T[]) new T[];
public static void main() {
Bar b = new Bar&lt;String&gt;();
}
}
Will they compile? Will they run? At a first glance it may seem that both make inappropriate casting from superclass Object[] to subclass String[].
